INSERT INTO schema_08.reviews_08(review_id, nickname, date_created, review_score, book_isbn, description) VALUES('2ddc09e29f1cf459d5cbfe2117616785','Jacqueline2dd', '{2016-06-06 10:38:22-07:00}', '4', '0152054456', 'Its impossible to read this book without thinking of the absolute decimation of Syria (and many other parts of the Middle East) right now. It can be so difficult to understand in any meaningful context what effects such violence have on real lives; we see it on the television every day, but it doesnt really *mean* anything tangible in the United States because we havent experienced anything nearly to that level of decimation in 150+ years. This little book does a good job of helping us to put things in perspective by focusing simply on the (true) story of a librarian in Basra who managed to save all of the books in the library to help preserve their history and continue educating the community before the library building was destroyed by a bomb. I wish the illustrations were a little more lush (its the only reason Im docking the book a star), but the story is spot on. It shows the grit and determination of extraordinary people in horrifying circumstances and how important the "little" things can be to maintaining normalcy and rebuilding once the conflict is over. This is a sweet story, and a good one for kids who are asking about Syria/Iraq/conflict and need something to help them understand it that isnt violent or gory.'); 
