 So, what do I think overall? I thought it was a great story line with great characters. Peter was the main character but not the only interesting one. The story is a stand alone, something I love and is totally complete with a very definite ending. But there is the hint that there could be more stories to come. And it would definitely be a shame to leave Peter Nimble and His Fantastic Eyes in the Vanished Kingdom. Jonathan Auxiers humor was subtle and honestly, it took me a lot longer to read this book than others this length. I think that was because it was truly more literary (I hate to say intelligent or smart so I hope you understand when I say literary) than any other MG novel Ive read. It didnt take away from my enjoyment of it at all. It probably increased it because it made it so unique. Sure you can read it as just a story, but I bet you cant breeze through it. Youll miss the humor. And it shouldnt be missed. I highly recommend Peter Nimble and His Fantastic Eyes.'); 
